The UK will not reverse the ban of miraa.Last Saturday, British High Commissioner Nic Hailey said, "We were the last major Western country to ban miraa. We did not target Kenya." He said the UK has funded other projects to provide alternative source of income to affected farmers.He paid a courtesy call to Meru county commissioner Wilfred Nyagwanga and Deputy Governor Raphael Muriungi. Hailey said Britain will continue to partner with Kenya in the tourism and agriculture sectors. He said Britons are some of the leading tourists.